                                    <list>
                                        <item>
                                            <p>Nine paper leaves, about 19 J in. by 13§ (Add.
                                                11,732, foil. 229—237), eight of which formed part
                                                of the eighth quire (ܚ) of a large manuscript. Foll.
                                                229, 232, 233, and 236, are much torn; and two
                                                leaves are wanting after fol. 232. Each page is
                                                divided into two columns of 31 lines. These leaves
                                                are written in a good, regular hand of the xiith
                                                cent.</p>
                                        </item>
                                    </list>
                                </condition>
